\begin_layout Standard
To quantify the error between predictions, a metric should be defined.
 For that purpose we define normalized root mean square error (NRMSE) as:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
e(t)=\frac{\left\Vert \hat{\psi}(t)-\psi(t)\right\Vert }{\left\Vert \psi(t)\right\Vert }\label{eq:error}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Together with this norm, we also consider the prediction horizon defined
 as: 
\begin_inset Formula $PH(\varepsilon)=\min_{t}e(t)\geq\varepsilon$
\end_inset

, The prediction horizon is the first time the NRMSE exceed tolerance 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

, in this study we consider case 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon=0.4$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The result of 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Nonlinear Transformation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We perform 100 realizations of RC simulation for each non-linear transformation
 described in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Reservoir-Computing"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Each realizations were optimized for the spectral radius by using Recycled
 Validation method.
 Our result agree with the result in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Barbosa2021"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 which emphasize the symmetry between RC and the modelled system.
 The odd quadratic transformation 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{2}$
\end_inset

 performed the best compared to the rest of transformation.
 The cubic transformation 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{3}$
\end_inset

 as expected performed better than 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{1}$
\end_inset

 which attributed to the odd symmetry of 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{3}$
\end_inset

.
 Despite the odd symmetry, the no transformation case perform poorly compared
 to 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 However, we observe that by using more nodes, the case without non-linear
 transformation slightly better compared with 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

